# API Response Conventions

Use simple, consistent HTTP response shapes from controllers.

## Success response shapes

- Detail endpoints (`GET /resource/:id`) return a single object.
- Create endpoints (`POST /resource`) return the created object (status `201`).
- List endpoints return an object with:
  - `items`: array of resources
  - `total`: total matching resources

```ts
// ✅ Detail
return employee;

// ✅ List
return { items, total };
```

## Avoid mixed/enveloped patterns by default

- Do not wrap all responses in `{ data: ... }` unless explicitly requested.
- Keep shape consistent across endpoints in the same module.

## Error handling alignment

- Controllers define HTTP contract and Swagger responses.
- Services throw typed exceptions (`NotFoundException`, `ConflictException`, etc.).
- Do not convert known typed errors into generic 500 responses in controllers.
